# Coding posture (Cursor)

Inside Cursor, **Grok** (e.g. Grok 4.5 high/fast) implements all coding — file writes, edits, scripts, config — unless Daniel explicitly says otherwise for that task.

- Do **not** default to Codex/`codex exec` for coding in Cursor.
- Planning, audits, and docs may still use other models when asked.
- Claude Code’s separate `codex-codes-gate` does not override this Cursor posture.
